videos.headline: Mukesh Kumar to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! That's the end of Dube who wasn't allowed to tee off tonight. Excellent execution of plans from DC to bowl it wide outside off. THis is a slower length ball, makes Dube reach out for the big hit and he flat-bats it straight to long-off. Shivam Dube c Tristan Stubbs b Mukesh Kumar 18(17) [4s-1]

Mukesh Kumar to Sameer Rizvi, out Caught by Khaleel Ahmed!! Well, this is how it goes in this format. Six off his first ball the other day, and now a golden duck. Good length delivery on off, he looks to play across the line, gets a leading edge and it flies to Khaleel at short third. He makes no mistake. Sameer Rizvi c Khaleel Ahmed b Mukesh Kumar 0(1)

Mukesh Kumar to Sameer Rizvi, out Caught by Khaleel Ahmed!! Well, this is how it goes in this format. Six off his first ball the other day, and now a golden duck. Mukesh Kumar to Rahane, out Caught by Warner!! Rahane looks to slog and perishes! Not really a strength of his. It's the situation that necessitates him to go for it, but he doesn't get hold. It's a slower ball floated up on off, Rahane looks to go over midwicket but slices it off the outside half. Simple catch for Warner at long-on. Rahane c Warner b Mukesh Kumar 45(30) [4s-5 6s-2]

Axar to Mitchell, out Caught&Bowled!! Simple return catch for Axar! Flat length ball on off, gets big on Mitchell as he looks to loft down the ground and hits him high on the bat resulting in a mishit. It goes to the left of Axar who takes a good low catch. Mitchell c and b Axar 34(26) [4s-1 6s-2]

Khaleel Ahmed to Ravindra, out Caught by Tristan Stubbs!! This wicket was always on the cards!! Khaleel was totally bossing this exchange and rightly gets the wicket. A short of length delivery, shapes away from off as Rachin tries a big swipe across the line. Top-edges it over the bowler's head and Stubbs from mid-off runs to his left to take a well judged catch. Both CSK openers out cheaply, that's been a rarity. Khaleel is in the middle of a dream spell out here... Ravindra c Tristan Stubbs b Khaleel Ahmed 2(12)

Khaleel Ahmed to Gaikwad, out Caught by Pant!! Superb inswinger from Khaleel, too good for Ruturaj. Jumps up and punches the air the delight. A length ball that pitches on off and moves devilishly inwards after pitching to get a faint inside edge onto the keeper. Delhi get the early wicket they would have desired, superb first over from Khaleel! Gaikwad c Pant b Khaleel Ahmed 1(2)

Pathirana to Pant, out Caught by Gaikwad!! Fifty and out!! A yorker length delivery onto off, Pant tried to get under it but this time toe-ends it high in the air. Felt like it might land safe but Ruturaj runs in from long-off and takes a solid, tumbling catch. Third wicket for Pathirana. Pant c Gaikwad b Pathirana 51(32) [4s-4 6s-3]

Pathirana to Tristan Stubbs, out Bowled!! Another one!! Another out of this world yorker from Matheesha Pathirana. And this time it castles a South African who's no newcomer to speed. 149.5 clicks, fast and knocks down the off and middle pole. Sri Lankan cricket, you have your successor to Malinga. His name is Matheesa Pathirana! A game changing over from the youngster Tristan Stubbs b Pathirana 0(2)

Pathirana to Mitchell Marsh, out Bowled!! Fast bowling at its finest!! To outdo an Aussie batter who's grown up on the wickets of Perth for pace shows how good a delivery that would have been from Matheesha Pathirana. 150 clicks, on the money with the yorker and rattles the stumps before the batter could get his bat down to block. Gets a bit of inward movement as well on that one, unplayable stuff!! Mitchell Marsh b Pathirana 18(12) [4s-2 6s-1]

Jadeja to Prithvi Shaw, out Caught by Dhoni!! Oh thick edge and MSD has held it! That wasn't an easy catch at all. Quicker delivery spinning away, Prithvi looks to cut, big deflection and Dhoni held his hands soft enough for the ball to nicely cushion into the gloves. Prithvi walks off without waiting for the finger. DC lose both set batters in quick succession. Prithvi will feel happy about that knock on return to the team. Prithvi Shaw c Dhoni b Jadeja 43(27) [4s-4 6s-2]

Mustafizur to Warner, out Caught by Pathirana!! Baby Malinga! Those slingers have helped him stretch his right hand really far back to pluck off this one-hander. Warner can't believe he's out to ball that he feels is a hit-me ball. Slower and full, Warner shapes up for the reverse-lap and actually hits it decently well, just that the placement wasn't right. Pathirana dives to his right and catches it behind his body. Ball just stucks in his fingertips. Prithvi pats Warner on the head as he walks off. End of a fine innings and the bowling change has worked for CSK. Warner c Pathirana b Mustafizur 52(35) [4s-5 6s-3]
